&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dermatology Clinical Nurse Specialist (Band 6)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part time – 20.5 hours&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Dermatology department has an exciting opportunity for a Band 6 Clinical Nurse Specialist to join our well established, friendly and expanding county wide team. We run a phototherapy service, have outpatient clinics at 3 hospital sites, undertake regular minor skin surgery lists and also offer Mohs micrographic surgery at Worcester Royal Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will be a team player able to support patient pathways in dermatology and participate fully in the treatment and monitoring of patients including those on systemic therapies. You will be an excellent communicator committed to ensuring high quality patient care. If you are motivated and keen to make a difference to people with Dermatological conditions we would like to hear from you. In return you will be well supported in this job role and welcomed to the team with exciting opportunities for further personal and professional development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact: Wendy Bramhall Band 7 Skin Oncology CNS 01905 733876 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;wbramhall@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; or Sheree Warner Dermatology Specialist Nurse / Phototherapist 01527 503030 ext 44518 or bleep 1031 or email Shereelyn.warner@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews to be held on Thursday 19th November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
